HIGH ABOVE THE CITY  ON A TALL COLUMN  STOOD THE STATUE OF THE HAPPY PRINCE  HE WAS GILDED ALL OVER WITH THIN LEAVES OF FINE GOLD  FOR EYES HE HAD TWO BRIGHT SAPPHIRES  AND A LARGE RED RUBY GLOWED ON HIS SWORD HILT 

HE WAS VERY MUCH ADMIRED INDEED  “HE IS AS BEAUTIFUL AS A WEATHERCOCK ” REMARKED ONE OF THE TOWN COUNCILLORS WHO WISHED TO GAIN A REPUTATION FOR HAVING ARTISTIC TASTES  “ONLY NOT QUITE SO USEFUL ” HE ADDED  FEARING LEST PEOPLE SHOULD THINK HIM UNPRACTICAL  WHICH HE REALLY WA